  "texts": [
    "Publishers have a tendency to prioritize different topics.",
    "This is especially prevalent for less mainstream publishers, which have far fewer resources to spend on the breadth of their reporting.",
    "It is therefore plausible that the 'Publisher' and 'Topic' splits have some overlap.",
    "We test for this by comparing the amount of article level overlap in the held-out test sets of the 'Publisher' and 'Topic' to random draws of the same size from uncorrelated uniform distributions.",
    "The larger this overlap, the more correlated the two test sets are."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}